primaryTopic.definition: CRCSI is an international research and development centre set up in 2003 under the Australian Government Business Cooperative Research Centres Programme. They conduct user-driven research in spatial information that address issues of national importance. They also perform commissioned research projects for key clients. Their partners, from both Australia and New Zealand, include federal and state government agencies, universities and over 50 companies.
